==English==
===Proverb===
'''[[great]] [[mind]]s [[think]] [[alike]] ([[fools]] [[seldom]] [[differ]])'''
# {{idiom}} used to emphasize a [[coincidence]], or two people reaching the same conclusion in any manner at the same time.
#: Person A: ''He looks a bit like [[w:David Beckham|David Beckham]]...''
#: Person B: ''I was just thinking that!''
#: Person A: '''''Great minds think alike''', eh!''
#: Person B: ''More like '''fools seldom differ''' in our cases...''

==== Usage note ====
The "Fools seldom differ" part is found in British English only.

==== Translations ====
*Chinese: [[英雄所見略同]], [[英雄所见略同]]
*French: [[les grands esprits se rencontrent]]


